cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about unsupervised figure-ground segmentation in images using a "learning to learn" approach. The paper focuses on exploring webly-abundant images of specific visual effects to learn the internal representations of these effects in an unsupervised manner. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a meta-learning process to learn to imitate visual effects, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with image editing and generative processes, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses neural networks to accomplish its task, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
